## 2. Repo Overview

### Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version / Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Runtime | Node.js | ≥ 20 LTS |
| Monorepo | Turborepo + pnpm | pnpm workspaces |
| Backend | NestJS | Modular monolith, REST |
| ORM | Prisma | PostgreSQL 16 |
| Cache/Queue | Redis + BullMQ | Redis provisioned, BullMQ not yet used |
| Web Frontend | Next.js | App Router (14.x) |
| Mobile | Expo + React Native | Shell only |
| Validation | class-validator + class-transformer | Whitelist mode globally |
| Auth | JWT (HS256) + Passport | Access 15m, Refresh 7d |
| API Docs | Swagger / OpenAPI | `http://localhost:3001/api/docs` |
| CI | GitHub Actions | `.github/` present |

### Entry Points

| App | Start Command | URL |
|---|---|---|
| API | `pnpm --filter api dev` | http://localhost:3001/api/v1 |
| Swagger | — | http://localhost:3001/api/docs |
| Web | `pnpm --filter web dev` | http://localhost:3000 |
| Mobile | `pnpm --filter mobile dev` | Expo Go / Metro |
| DB Studio | `pnpm db:studio` | Prisma Studio GUI |

### Key Config Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `turbo.json` | Turborepo pipeline (dev, build, test, lint) |
| `pnpm-workspace.yaml` | Workspace = `apps/*`, `packages/*` |
| `docker-compose.yml` | PostgreSQL 5432, Redis 6379 |
| `.env.example` (root + `apps/api`) | All env var keys documented |
| `apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma` | 1053-line schema, single source of DB truth |
| `apps/api/src/main.ts` | Global prefix `/api/v1`, Helmet, CORS, ValidationPipe, Swagger |
| `apps/api/src/app.module.ts` | 19 modules registered |

### How to Run Locally

```bash
pnpm install
cp .env.example .env        # set JWT_SECRET (min 32 chars)
pnpm docker:up              # starts Postgres + Redis
pnpm db:generate && pnpm db:migrate && pnpm db:seed
pnpm --filter api dev       # API on :3001
pnpm --filter web dev       # Web on :3000
```

Default super-admin: `admin@bms.local` / `Admin@123456`

> [!CAUTION]
> The seed credentials are **hardcoded in `.env.example`** (line 56: `SEED_ADMIN_PASSWORD=Admin@123456`). This is a dev convenience but must not reach production.

