## 3. Architecture & Data Flow

```
┌─────────────────── Client Applications ─────────────────────────────┐
│  Next.js (apps/web)       Expo Mobile (apps/mobile)                  │
│  Admin Portal - :3000     Student App (shell only)                   │
└───────────────┬──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
                │  HTTPS REST          │  HTTPS REST
                ▼                      ▼
┌─────────── API Gateway (apps/api/src/main.ts) ──────────────────────┐
│  Helmet (CSP, HSTS)     CORS (origin: FRONTEND_URL only)            │
│  ThrottlerGuard (10/s short, 30/min medium — global)                │
│  Global Prefix: /api/v1   Swagger: /api/docs                        │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────┘
                           │
┌─────────── NestJS Application (app.module.ts) ──────────────────────┐
│                                                                      │
│  auth       users      hostels    buildings   policies   students    │
│  allotments leave      complaints notices     gate       violations  │
│  notifications  registration  uploads  dashboard  audit   health     │
│                                                                      │
│  Cross-cutting: JwtAuthGuard → RolesGuard → AuditInterceptor        │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────┘
                           │  Prisma ORM
        ┌──────────────────┼─────────────────┐
        ▼                  ▼                 ▼
   PostgreSQL:5432     Redis:6379         uploads/
   (20 models)         (provisioned,      (local disk,
   Migrations done     not consumed)      no S3 yet)
```

### Critical Auth Flow

```
POST /auth/login (5/min throttle)
  → AuthService.login()
  → find user by email|mobile|usn
  → bcrypt.compare(password, hash)
  → sign accessToken (15m) + refreshToken (7d)
  → store hash(refreshToken) in RefreshToken table

POST /auth/refresh (10/min throttle)
  → validate refreshToken hash in DB
  → reuse detection: if already revoked → revoke ALL user tokens
  → issue new pair (rotation)

GET /auth/me (JwtAuthGuard)
  → decode JWT → load user + roles + permissions

POST /auth/logout (JwtAuthGuard)
  → revokedAt = now() on ALL user refresh tokens
```

